      <pubDate>Sat, 25 Apr 2020 14:11:49 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://blog.jverkamp.com/2020/04/25/crescent-dawn/</guid>
      <description>&lt;figure class=&#34;cover-image&#34;&gt;
                &lt;a data-goodreads-type=&#34;book&#34; data-goodreads-id=&#34;8219033&#34; href=&#34;https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/8219033.crescent-dawn&#34;&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://blog.jverkamp.com/embeds/books/crescent-dawn.jpg&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
            &lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The deliveryman smiled as he eyed the thick stack of currency. “I wonder if the Germans would pay this much to sink a ship and murder a general,” he said. “You wouldn’t happen to be working for the Kaiser, now, would you?”&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The minister firmly shook his head. “No, this is a theological matter. Had you been able to locate the document, this would not have been necessary.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;</description>
